<span id="freeTextContainer16675135586312920588">This is a beautifully written fiction of the life of Christ that focuses on the human aspect of the savior. Rather than assuming that Jesus knew what would happen through the course of time, Kazantzakis shows how Jesus struggles with events and temptations and still manages to triumph. Aside from the beautifully written prose, what I liked most about this book is how it makes the person of Jesus more accessible to the average person by focusing on His struggles. In addition, the author does a wo</span>
  <span id="freeText16675135586312920588" style="display:none">This is a beautifully written fiction of the life of Christ that focuses on the human aspect of the savior. Rather than assuming that Jesus knew what would happen through the course of time, Kazantzakis shows how Jesus struggles with events and temptations and still manages to triumph. Aside from the beautifully written prose, what I liked most about this book is how it makes the person of Jesus more accessible to the average person by focusing on His struggles. In addition, the author does a wonderful job of fictionalizing how/ why Judas would betray Jesus. Rather than simply vilifying the action, we get to watch Judas go through his own struggles as he also seeks to do what he believes to be the right thing.<br /><br />This is a book that will make you think and give you an interesting perspective on stories that many of us have heard repeatedly. If you enjoy stretching your mind and are comfortable with challenging your own beliefs you will probably enjoy this book.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16675135586312920588" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
